Using statistics based on values ranked at the grid point or very local level therefore poses a major problem
at the global, continental, and regional scales as it severely in
ates the uncertainty as represented by model
spread. An important consequence of this
nding is that impact analyses relying on multimodel information
based on grid point ranked statistics will indicate a likelihood of highly unwanted future impacts, a risk
ated uncertainty and unlikely to be physically realizable. Such analyses may
lead to costly overadaptation and hence maladaptation. These caveats should be carefully considered when
multimodel projections are used in impact studies, and any selection of subensembles should be based on
